      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-core): write Deep Sleep summary into DREAMS.md after deep dreaming phase (fixes #91051)",
        "body": "**Summary**: The deep dreaming phase writes its structured report to `memory/dreaming/deep/YYYY-MM-DD.md` but never updates the `## Deep Sleep` section in `DREAMS.md` as documented.\n\n**Root Cause**: `writeDeepDreamingReport()` in `dreaming-markdown.ts` only writes to the separate report file under `memory/dreaming/deep/`. There is no corresponding write to `DREAMS.md` for the `## Deep Sleep` summary block. Unlike the light and REM phases that write managed blocks to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`, the deep phase had no path to populate `DREAMS.md` with its structured summary (ranked/promoted counts).\n\n**Fix**: Added `writeDeepDreamingToDreamsMd()` in `dreaming-markdown.ts` that writes a `## Deep Sleep` managed block (with `<!-- openclaw:dreaming:deep:start -->` / `<!-- openclaw:dreaming:deep:end -->` markers) into `DREAMS.md`. Called from the deep dreaming sweep in `dreaming.ts` immediately after `writeDeepDreamingReport()`.\n\n**Verification**:\n- `pnpm build` — passes\n- `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-markdown.test.ts` — 5 tests pass\n- `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming.test.ts` — 50 tests pass\n- `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-narrative.test.ts` — 96 tests pass\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: After a deep dreaming phase sweep, `DREAMS.md` now receives a `## Deep Sleep` section summarizing ranked/promoted counts, matching the documented behavior.\n\n**Real environment tested**:\n- OS: Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64\n- Node: v22.22.0\n- OpenClaw: 2026.6.1 (66b91d78feb33d62e2f82ae1d8689c48519f5530)\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n1. `pnpm build` — builds cleanly\n2. `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-markdown.test.ts` — all tests pass\n3. `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming.test.ts` — all 50 tests pass\n\n**Evidence after fix**: Verified with real file I/O in an isolated temp directory. The function correctly writes a `## Deep Sleep` managed block into `DREAMS.md`:\n\nFresh workspace (no existing DREAMS.md):\n```\n## Deep Sleep\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:deep:start -->\n- Ranked 5 candidate(s).\n- Promoted 2 candidate(s).\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:deep:end -->\n```\n\nIdempotent update (subsequent run replaces the block):\n```\n## Deep Sleep\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:deep:start -->\n- Ranked 7 candidate(s).\n- Promoted 4 candidate(s).\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:deep:end -->\n```\n\nExisting DREAMS.md with other content — the managed block is appended without disturbing existing content:\n```\n# Dream Diary\n\nSome existing content\n\n## Deep Sleep\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:deep:start -->\n- Repaired recall artifacts: 0 stale entries.\n- Ranked 8 candidate(s) for durable promotion.\n- Promoted 3 candidate(s) into MEMORY.md.\n<!-- openclaw:dreaming:deep:end -->\n```\n\nSource: [extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-markdown.ts](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-markdown.ts)\n\n**Observed result after fix**: Three scenarios tested with real file I/O in isolated temp directories — all produce correct `## Deep Sleep` managed blocks. `pnpm test` for all memory-core dreaming tests exits 0 (151 tests pass across 3 test files). The function correctly handles fresh workspace, idempotent update, and existing DREAMS.md with unrelated content.\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end cron-driven deep dreaming sweep with a live gateway was not tested in this environment.\n\n**Regression Test Plan**:\n- `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-markdown.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-narrative.test.ts`\n- `pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-phases.test.ts`\n\n**Review Findings Addressed**: N/A (new PR)\n\n**Merge Risk**: Low. The change adds a new function call immediately after an existing write; it does not modify any existing behavior. The new function follows the same managed block pattern already used throughout memory-core (`replaceManagedMarkdownBlock`). If DREAMS.md does not exist, it is created. The managed block is scoped to `## Deep Sleep` markers and will not interfere with the diary section managed by the narrative code.\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-91051-deep-sleep-dreams-md",
